text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia newbeyi is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Pulchellae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Great Southern regions of Western Australia.The openly branched and pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 1 metre (1 to 3 ft). It blooms from July to August and produces yellow flowers.
